title="Sandwich operators and Einstein deformations of compact symmetric spaces related to Jordan algebras">[hall-2024-sandwich]</fr:link></fr:meta></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>A Jordan algebra <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[(J,\circ )]]></fr:tex> is called <html:dfn
xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">formally real</html:dfn> whenever for any <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[n\in \mathbb {N}]]></fr:tex> and for any <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[x_{1},…,x_{n}\in  J]]></fr:tex>, we have:</fr:p><fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[x_{1}^{2}+\cdots +x_{n}^{2}=0\quad \hbox {implies}\quad  x_{1}=\cdots =x_{n}=0]]></fr:tex><fr:p>Observe <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[(\mathbb {R},\circ )]]></fr:tex> is formally real.</fr:p><fr:p>We can decompose formally real Jordan algebras into the direct sum of <fr:link
type="local"
href="jordan-0005.xml"
addr="jordan-0005"
title="Simple Jordan algebra">simple</fr:link> Jordan algebras.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree><fr:tree
